def statistics(data):
    n = data.shape[0]
    mean = np.mean(data)
    variance = np.var(data)
    log_likelihood = -((n*m.log(np.pi)/2)) - ((n* m.log(variance)/2) - (n/2))
    return mean, variance, log_likelihood

#Adopted from unutbu, Apr 13th, 2012, Stackoverflow (https://stackoverflow.com/a/10138308)
import matplotlib.mlab as mlab
def plotNorm(mean, variance, scalingfactor):
    sigma = np.sqrt(variance)
    x = np.linspace(mean-scalingfactor*variance, mean+scalingfactor*variance, 100)
    plt.plot(x, mlab.normpdf(x, mean, sigma))
    plt.show()

#Part 1
#Power Iteration Routine
def powerIteration(X):
    v_i = np.random.rand(X.shape[1], 1)
    for i in range(5000):
        v_i = np.dot(X,v_i)
        v_i /= np.linalg.norm(v_i)
    return v_i

def g(x):
    for i in range(x.shape[0]):
        for j in range(x.shape[1]):
            x[i][j] = 1/(1+np.exp(-x[i][j]))
    return x

def g_prime(x):
    for i in range(x.shape[0]):
        for j in range(x.shape[1]):
            x[i][j] = np.exp(-x[i][j])/(1 + np.exp(-x[i][j]))**2
    return x

def generate_image(denoising_filter, X, allowable_range_w, allowable_range_h):
    denoised_image = np.reshape(np.dot(denoising_filter.T,X),(allowable_range_w, allowable_range_w))
    return denoised_image
In [46]:
filter_size = 3
def denoising(image_train, image_target, filter_size):
    w = image_train.shape[0] #Width of Input Image
    h = image_train.shape[1] #Height of Input Image
    
    #
    denoising_filter = np.random.uniform(0.0,1.0,(filter_size, filter_size)) 
    
    
    X = []
    allowable_range_w = w - filter_size
    allowable_range_h = h - filter_size
    N = allowable_range_w*allowable_range_h
    for i in range(allowable_range_w):
        x = []
        for j in range(allowable_range_h):          
            x = image_train[i:i+filter_size, j:j+filter_size].reshape(-1).tolist()
            X.append(x)
    

    #Converting image into Row matrix
    X = (np.array(X)).T
    denoising_filter = np.reshape(np.ravel(denoising_filter), (filter_size**2,1))
    
    denoised_image = np.ones((allowable_range_w, allowable_range_h))
    
    for i in range(allowable_range_w):
        for j in range(allowable_range_h):
            denoised_image[i][j] = image_target[i][j]
            
    image = generate_image(denoising_filter,X, allowable_range_w, allowable_range_h)
    
    error = []

    rho = 0.1 #step size
    for i in range(1000):
        G = g(image)
        G_Prime = g_prime(image)
        ElementWiseProduct = (np.multiply((denoised_image - G),G_Prime)).T
        ElementWiseProduct = np.reshape(np.ravel(ElementWiseProduct), ((allowable_range_w*allowable_range_h), 1))
        image1 = -(2/(allowable_range_w*allowable_range_h))*X
        delta = np.dot(image1,ElementWiseProduct)
        denoising_filter = denoising_filter - (rho * delta)
        image = generate_image(denoising_filter,X, allowable_range_w, allowable_range_h)
        error_value = denoised_image - G 
        error_value = (np.reshape(np.ravel(error_value), (N, 1)))
        convergence_factor = 1/(np.dot(error_value.T,error_value))
        error.append((convergence_factor).tolist()[0][0])
    print("Resultant Image:")
    plt.imshow(image)
    plt.gray()
    plt.show()
    print("Convergence Plot")
    plt.plot(error)
    plt.xlabel('Iterations')
    plt.ylabel('Error')
    plt.show()

#Support Functions for BFGS
def g(x):
    for i in range(x.shape[0]):
        for j in range(x.shape[1]):
            x[i][j] = 1/(1+np.exp(-x[i][j]))
    return x

def g_prime(x):
    for i in range(x.shape[0]):
        for j in range(x.shape[1]):
            x[i][j] = np.exp(-x[i][j])/((1 + np.exp(-x[i][j]))**2)
    return x

def term_1(p,v):

    return (np.divide((np.dot(p,p.T)), np.dot(p.T, v)))


def term_2(G,v):

    numerator = np.dot(np.dot(np.dot(G,v),v.T), G)
    denominator = np.dot(np.dot(v.T, G), v)

    return (np.divide(numerator, denominator))


def term_3(G,v,u):
    return ((np.dot(np.dot(v.T,G),v))*(np.dot(u,u.T)))

def U(p,v,G):

    first = np.divide(p, np.dot(p.T,v))
    second = np.divide(np.dot(G,v), np.dot(np.dot(v.T,G),v))
    return (first-second)

def generate_image(denoising_filter,x):
    denoised_image = np.reshape(np.dot(denoising_filter.T,x),(197,197))
    return denoised_image

filter_size = 3

def bfgs_desnoising(image_train, image_target, filter_size):
    w = image_train.shape[0]
    h = image_train.shape[1]
    allowable_range_w = w - filter_size
    allowable_range_h = h - filter_size
    N = allowable_range_w * allowable_range_h
    #Initial Filter
    denoising_filter = np.random.uniform(0.0,1.0,(filter_size, filter_size))
    X = []

    for i in range(allowable_range_w):
        x = []
        for j in range(allowable_range_w):
            x = image_train[i:i+filter_size, j: j+filter_size].reshape(-1).tolist()
            X.append(x)

    X = (np.array(X)).T

    
    denoising_filter = np.reshape(np.ravel(denoising_filter), (filter_size**2,1))
    denoised_image = np.ones((197, 197))

    for i in range(allowable_range_w):
        for j in range(allowable_range_h):
            denoised_image[i][j] = image_target[i][j]


    image = generate_image(denoising_filter,X)
    #Initialize G | Inverse Hessian Matrix (G=inv(H))
    G_i = np.identity(9)

    #First Iteration outside loop
    
    #step-size
    rho = 0.1
    G = g(image)
    G_Prime = g_prime(image)
    ElementWiseProduct = (np.multiply(( - G),G_Prime)).T
    ElementWiseProduct = np.reshape(np.ravel(ElementWiseProduct), (N, 1))
    X1 = (2/(N))*X

    # Delta_F_i
    delta_previous = np.dot(X1,ElementWiseProduct)

    #Filter_i+1
    denoising_filter_next = denoising_filter + (rho * delta_previous)

    image = generate_image(denoising_filter_next,X1)

    denoised_G = g(denoised_image)
    error = []

    for i in range(6):
        G = g(image)
        G_Prime = g_prime(image)
        ElementWiseProduct = (np.multiply((denoised_image  - G),G_Prime)).T
        ElementWiseProduct = np.reshape(np.ravel(ElementWiseProduct), (N, 1))
        X1 = (2/(N))*X


        # Delta_F_i+1
        delta = np.dot(X1,ElementWiseProduct)

        #Parameters
        #p
        p = denoising_filter_next - denoising_filter

        #v
        v = delta - delta_previous

        #u
        u = U(p,v,G_i)

        #G_i+1
        G_i = G_i + term_1(p,v) + term_2(G_i,v) + term_3(G_i,v,u)

        #Step sizing G
        G_i = rho*G_i

        denoising_filter = denoising_filter_next


        denoising_filter_next = denoising_filter - np.dot(G_i,delta_previous)
        image = generate_image(denoising_filter_next,X1)

        delta_previous = delta

        error_value = (denoised_G-G)
        error_value = (np.reshape(np.ravel(error_value), (N, 1)))
        convergence_factor = 1/(np.dot(error_value.T,error_value))
        error.append((convergence_factor).tolist()[0][0])
    print("Resultant Image:")
    plt.imshow(image)
    plt.gray()
    plt.show()
    print("Convergence Plot")
    plt.plot(error)
    plt.xlabel('Iterations')
    plt.ylabel('Error')
    plt.show()
